section.section:
The insurer may include in the provision set forth in subsection (a) of this section a definition of "valid loss-of-time coverage" if the definition:
is approved as to form by the Commissioner;
is limited to:
coverage provided by governmental units or organizations subject to regulation by insurance law or insurance authorities of this State, another state, or a province of Canada;
any other coverage that the Commissioner may approve for inclusion; or
a combination of these coverages.
